verbs.description: overnet (third-person singular simple present overnets, present participle overnetting, simple past and past participle overnetted)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To cover with a net or netting.
examples: Just beyond, creosote posts were overnetted with chicken wire, on which church ladies in summer spread tablecloths and set out food.

entries.meaning: To fish too much using nets.
